  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nAfter #46193 k8s master started rsyncing `.git` directory, causing hundreds of megabytes to be transferred, making some workflows that utilize remote docker engines impractical. E.g. I use [kubeadm-dind-cluster](https://github.com/Mirantis/kubeadm-dind-cluster) which can start docker-in-docker test cluster on the same remote docker where k8s is built, and currently my Internet connection can only give me about 1 Mb/s, so ~430Mb transfer caused by .git is impractical.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n`.git` is ignored as before, unless it's needed by the current script. In case `.git` is about to be `rsync`ed, a warning needs to be printed.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nJust run `build/run.sh`. Doing so against a remote docker over slow(ish) Internet connection will make the behavior apparent.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nFor now perhaps only `update-staging-godeps` script needs to rsync `.git` IIUC (see #46193).\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n654de23cbf821cd8b47387308de9a62aebb6df0d\r\n\r\nI'll work on this issue.\r\n",
